2500|$|Using Lull's example, a {{ship that}} {{intended}} to sail southeast ("Exaloch" [...] is Catalan for [...] "Scirocco") but was instead forced to sail east ("Levant"), then the angle of difference is θ=45°. [...] After 100 miles on the erroneous route, the <b>miliaria</b> on the intended route is 100cos45° = 70.71. [...] Doubling the sailing on the erroneous route to 200 miles will double the <b>miliaria</b> on the intended route to 141.42 miles (=200cos45°).|$|E
