50|$|The {{symptoms}} {{relating to}} <b>miliaria</b> {{should not be}} confused with shingles as they can be very similar. Shingles will restrict itself to one side of the body but also has a rash-like appearance. It is also accompanied by a prickling sensation and pain throughout the region. Those who suspect they have shingles and not <b>miliaria</b> should seek medical advice immediately as the sooner antivirals are taken, the better.|$|E
